schedules.task:
Query Sentry for the top unresolved issue with the most occurrences. Use the Sentry API to fetch org-wide issues sorted by priority and event count. Return ONLY the single issue with the highest event count in this format:

*Top Sentry Error:*
<https://sentry.io/organizations/$SENTRY_ORG/issues/{id}/|{title}> — `{project}`
• Events: {count} | Users: {userCount}
• Level: {level}
• Culprit: `{culprit}`
• First seen: {firstSeen} · Last seen: {lastSeen}

If there are no unresolved issues, output exactly: NO_OUTPUT

Use this command:
curl -s "https://sentry.io/api/0/organizations/$SENTRY_ORG/issues/?query=is:unresolved&sort=priority&limit=10" -H "Authorization: Bearer $SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN" | jq '[.[] | {id, title, culprit, project: .project.slug, count, userCount, firstSeen, lastSeen, level}] | sort_by(-.count) | first'
